{{BLP sources|date=October 2017}} '''Arstanbek Abdyldayev''' (born April 28, 1968) is a [[Kyrgyzstan|Kyrgyz]] politician and businessman, who was one of the candidates in the [[Kyrgyz presidential election, 2011|2011 presidential election]], most famous for his promise that there would be no winter, and the West would suffer from floods.<ref>[http://kloop.kg/blog/2011/12/14/zima-ne-budet-priblizhaetsya-k-200-ty-syacham-prosmotram-na-yutube/] «Зима не будет» приближается к 200 тысячам просмотрам на «Ютубе»</ref> The video of him telling about this became an [[Internet meme]] in the former [[Soviet Union]], with the most popular video about him gathering more than two million views on [[YouTube]].<ref name="This is horosho">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6xzBvkNra3A] Abdyldayev mentioned in the edition of "This is Horosho", a Russian-language internet show about memes</ref> Abdyldayev is participating in the [[Kyrgyz presidential election, 2017|2017 presidential election]] as an independent.
==Career==
Abdyldayev, a businessman born in [[Naryn Region]] of Kyrgyzstan,<ref>[http://who.ca-news.org/people/12311] Arstanbek Abdyldayev bio on AKIpress (Russian)</ref> is the founder of [[El Uchun]] party. He took part in 2011 presidential election in Kyrgyzstan but gained less than 0,5 percent, taking the 9th place out of 16 candidates.<ref>[http://www.shailoo.gov.kg/Itogi/] 2011 Kyrgyz presidential election preliminary results</ref>
He gained an immediate fame after holding a press conference shortly after the election, where he declared that there would be no winter in Kyrgyzstan, and that his home country is the core of the Earth.<ref name="This is horosho" />
