|The Caymans
|Mauritius
|Panama
}}

The second [[Institute on Taxation and Economic Policy]] list (Figure 4, page 16), is based on the reported profits of U.S. Fortune 500 controlled subsidiaries in 2013.  It tries to capture the scale of taxes shielded by looking at reported profits as a proxy.  Ireland now jumps to 2nd place, only just behind the Netherlands. The Netherlands-Ireland-Bermuda are usually the jurisdictions behind most "[[double Irish]] with a [[Dutch sandwich]]" BEPS schemes.<ref name="nyt"/>  Identical list to Zucman's list but with the Caribbean broken out into individual jurisdictions (the Caymans, Bermuda, Bahamas and the BVI).<ref name="ITEP">{{cite web|url=https://itep.org/wp-content/uploads/offshoreshellgames2017.pdf|title=Offshore Shell Games 2017|page=17|publisher=Institute of Taxation and Economic Policy|date=2017}}</ref>

