===Bloomberg Corporate tax inversions===

A simple but effective proxy are the destinations to where U.S. multinationals execute [[tax inversion]]s (i.e. an important test of the attractiveness of a corporate tax haven).  However, cases like inversions to Canada could reflect more of a "relative-tax" view (i.e. Canada offers lower taxes than the U.S. and it is close by and less controversial), than an "absolute-tax" view on the best global locations for a corporate tax haven.  The list still captures much of Zucman's list, particularly for the EU and the Caribbean. It captures the popularity of Ireland and the rise of the U.K.

Destinations for the 85 U.S. corporate inversions, since the first inversion in 1982, to the most recent inversion in 2016:<ref name="bbb"/>
