[[File:Swietelsky logo.svg|thumb|200px|Swietelsky company logo]] '''Hellmuth Swietelsky''' (23 March 1905 in [[Traiskirchen]]; 23 February 1995 in [[Zell am See]]) was an Austrian businessman and founder of the construction company {{ill|Swietelsky Baugesellschaft m.b.H|de|Swietelsky}}.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.aeiou.at/aeiou.encyclop.s/s988859.htm|title=Swietelsky, Hellmuth|website=www.aeiou.at|access-date=2017-10-19}}</ref>
Swietelsky was born in Traiskirchen ([[Lower Austria]]) in 23 March 1905. In 1936 he founded the company Swietelsky in [[Gmunden]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swietelsky.com/de/konzern/geschichte/|title=Geschichte|website=www.swietelsky.com|language=de|access-date=2017-10-19}}</ref>
In 1978 the [[University of Vienna]] awearded him the title ''Honorary senator of the University of Vienna'' (German: ''Ehrensenatoren der Technischen Universität Wien'').<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tuwien.ac.at/wir_ueber_uns/zahlen_und_fakten/akademische_wuerdentraeger_innen/|title=Technische Universität Wien : Akademische Würdenträger_innen|website=www.tuwien.ac.at|language=de|access-date=2017-10-19}}</ref> He was also an honorary president of the ''Austrian society of street construction'' and was a founding member of the [[ÖAMTC]], an Austrian automobile club.<ref name=":0" />
