[[File:Josef Sachs, 1872-1949 - Nordiska Museet - NMA.0034328.jpg|thumbnail|left|Photo of Sachs, taken 1900-1920.]] '''Josef Ernst Sachs''' was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] businessman and one of the two founders of the [[Nordiska Kompaniet]] department store in [[Stockholm]].
Born on January 4, 1872 in Stockholm, he became a student there in 1890. Devoteing himself to commercial exercises abroad, upon his return he worked with his father and later became president of the Josef Leja department store in 1902.<ref>{{cite book |last=Various |first= |date=1916 |title= Nordisk familjebok|trans-title=|url= http://runeberg.org/nfcd/0158.html|language= Swedish|location= |publisher= |isbn= |accessdate=July 5, 2914 }}</ref> He would later serve as president of Nordiska Kompaniet from 1902–37, Deputy Chairman of the Board 1933-44, then chairman of the firm until his death in 1949.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://digitaltmuseum.se/things/josef-sachs-1872-1949-kpman-vd-i-nordiska/S-NM/NMA.0034328|title=Josef Sachs, 1872-1949, köpman, VD i No...|language=Swedish |last1= Historian of the Digitalt Museum|first1= |last2= |first2= |date= 2013|website= digitaltmuseum.se|publisher= |accessdate=July 5, 2014}}</ref>
